@page "/"

<PageTitle>Polly Resiliency Patterns Demo</PageTitle>

<h1>🛡️ .NET Resiliency with Polly v8</h1>

<div class="alert alert-primary">
    <h4>Welcome to the Polly Resiliency Patterns Demo!</h4>
    <p>This demo application showcases various resiliency patterns using <strong>Polly v8</strong> in a .NET Aspire
        application.</p>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <h3>🎯 What You'll Learn</h3>
        <ul class="list-group">
            <li class="list-group-item">
                <strong>🔄 Retry Pattern:</strong> Handle transient failures with exponential backoff and jitter
            </li>
            <li class="list-group-item">
                <strong>⚡ Circuit Breaker:</strong> Fail fast when services are consistently unavailable
            </li>
            <li class="list-group-item">
                <strong>⏰ Timeout Pattern:</strong> Cancel long-running operations to maintain responsiveness
            </li>
            <li class="list-group-item">
                <strong>🚦 Rate Limiting:</strong> Control the rate of requests to protect downstream services
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6">
        <h3>🏗️ Architecture</h3>
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
                <p><strong>Frontend:</strong> Blazor Server with interactive components</p>
                <p><strong>Backend:</strong> ASP.NET Core Web API with simulated failures</p>
                <p><strong>Orchestration:</strong> .NET Aspire 9 for service discovery and resilience</p>
                <p><strong>Resiliency:</strong> Polly v8 with modern resilience pipelines</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-3">
            <a href="/weather" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">
                🚀 Start Demo
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="mt-4">
    <div class="card bg-light">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5>💡 Pro Tips for Your Presentation</h5>
            <ul>
                <li>Open browser developer tools (F12) to see detailed logging</li>
                <li>Try the Circuit Breaker multiple times quickly to see it open</li>
                <li>The API endpoints have different failure characteristics for realistic demos</li>
                <li>Each pattern shows timing and success/failure metrics</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

       